main event: A silver-yellow oval-cigar shaped object was observed by two teenage boys in Dudley, Massachusetts on July 17, 1965.
interesting points: The object was approximately the size of a pencil at arm's length.
The object moved left, then right, then remained stationary for about 15 minutes before disappearing straight up.
The observers tried to view the object through a telescope but were unable to due to tree branches blocking the view.
Weather conditions at the time included clear skies, light winds, and intermittent thunderstorms.
The observers were described as 17 and 16 years old, with their reliability unable to be judged.
result: Possible astro (aircraft) and possible variable light observation, with insufficient data to determine a valid conclusion.
